messages.message:
Invoking: `validate` with `{'patch': "--- a/ext/dom/php_dom.c\n+++ b/ext/dom/php_dom.c\n@@ -1483,10 +1483,18 @@ void dom_namednode_iter(dom_object *basenode, int ntype, dom_object *intern, xmlHashTablePtr ht, const char *local, size_t local_len, const char *ns, size_t ns_len)\n \t\tmapptr->local_lower = BAD_CAST estrdup(local);\n-\t\tif (len < 0) {\n-\t\t\tzend_str_tolower((char *) mapptr->local_lower, strlen((const char *) mapptr->local_lower));\n-\t\t} else {\n-\t\t\tzend_str_tolower((char *) mapptr->local_lower, len);\n-\t\t}\n+\t\tif (len < 0) {\n+\t\t\tzend_str_tolower((char *) mapptr->local_lower, strlen((const char *) mapptr->local_lower));\n+\t\t} else {\n+\t\t\t/* Allocate enough space for len bytes + null terminator */\n+\t\t\tmapptr->local_lower = BAD_CAST estrndup(local, len);\n+\t\t\t/* Ensure null-termination */\n+\t\t\t((char *)mapptr->local_lower)[len] = '\\0';\n+\t\t\tzend_str_tolower((char *) mapptr->local_lower, len);\n+\t\t}\n"}`
responded: The root cause of the heap buffer overflow is that `estrdup(local)` allocates a buffer of `strlen(local) + 1` bytes (for the null terminator), but the code then calls `zend_str_tolower((char *) mapptr->local_lower, len);` where `len` can be less than, equal to, or greater than `strlen(local)`. If `len` is greater than the actual string length, this will cause a buffer overflow.

**Correct fix:**
- Use `estrndup(local, len)` instead of `estrdup(local)` to ensure the buffer is at least `len + 1` bytes.
- When `len < 0`, use the string length as before.
- When `len >= 0`, ensure the buffer is allocated for `len` bytes, and the string is properly null-terminated.

Here is the patch:

```diff
--- a/ext/dom/php_dom.c
+++ b/ext/dom/php_dom.c
@@ -1483,10 +1483,18 @@ void dom_namednode_iter(dom_object *basenode, int ntype, dom_object *intern, xmlHashTablePtr ht, const char *local, size_t local_len, const char *ns, size_t ns_len)
 		mapptr->local_lower = BAD_CAST estrdup(local);
-		if (len < 0) {
-			zend_str_tolower((char *) mapptr->local_lower, strlen((const char *) mapptr->local_lower));
-		} else {
-			zend_str_tolower((char *) mapptr->local_lower, len);
-		}
+		if (len < 0) {
+			zend_str_tolower((char *) mapptr->local_lower, strlen((const char *) mapptr->local_lower));
+		} else {
+			/* Allocate enough space for len bytes + null terminator */
+			mapptr->local_lower = BAD_CAST estrndup(local, len);
+			/* Ensure null-termination */
+			((char *)mapptr->local_lower)[len] = '\0';
+			zend_str_tolower((char *) mapptr->local_lower, len);
+		}
```

