Invoking: `validate` with `{'patch': '--- a/ext/dom/php_dom.c
+++ b/ext/dom/php_dom.c
@@ -1482,10 +1482,18 @@
 		}
-		mapptr->local_lower = BAD_CAST estrdup(local);
-		if (len < 0) {
-			zend_str_tolower((char *) mapptr->local_lower, strlen((const char *) mapptr->local_lower));
-		} else {
-			zend_str_tolower((char *) mapptr->local_lower, len);
-		}
+		if (len < 0) {
+			mapptr->local_lower = BAD_CAST estrdup(local);
+			zend_str_tolower((char *) mapptr->local_lower, strlen((const char *) mapptr->local_lower));
+		} else {
+			mapptr->local_lower = BAD_CAST estrndup(local, len);
+			zend_str_tolower((char *) mapptr->local_lower, len);
+		}
 	}
'}`
responded: The root cause of the heap buffer overflow is that `estrdup(local)` allocates a buffer of size `strlen(local)+1`, but the code later calls `zend_str_tolower((char *) mapptr->local_lower, len)`, where `len` may be less than, equal to, or greater than `strlen(local)`. If `len > strlen(local)`, this will write past the end of the buffer, causing a heap buffer overflow.

The correct fix is to use `estrndup(local, len)` instead of `estrdup(local)` when `len >= 0`, so the allocated buffer is always at least `len+1` bytes. When `len < 0`, `estrdup(local)` is fine, and the code uses `strlen()` for the length.

Let's prepare the patch for `ext/dom/php_dom.c` to fix this.

args.patch:
diff --git a/ext/dom/php_dom.c b/ext/dom/php_dom.c
index 939c1794520..f1bec4227db 100644
--- a/ext/dom/php_dom.c
+++ b/ext/dom/php_dom.c
@@ -1480,10 +1480,11 @@ void dom_namednode_iter(dom_object *basenode, int ntype, dom_object *intern, xml
 			mapptr->local = xmlCharStrndup(local, len);
 			mapptr->free_local = true;
 		}
-		mapptr->local_lower = BAD_CAST estrdup(local);
 		if (len < 0) {
+			mapptr->local_lower = BAD_CAST estrdup(local);
 			zend_str_tolower((char *) mapptr->local_lower, strlen((const char *) mapptr->local_lower));
 		} else {
+			mapptr->local_lower = BAD_CAST estrndup(local, len);
 			zend_str_tolower((char *) mapptr->local_lower, len);
 		}
 	}
